ory:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Gravesend, Kent]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Kent]]\n\n\n{{England-tv-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "LadyLamorna", "label": "safe", "comment": "grammatical correction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Simmons"}
{"title_page": "3 Will Be Free", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Thai action drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = 3 Will Be Free\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|th|\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14}}\n| image                    = 3 Will Be Free poster.jpg\n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = {{ubl\n|[[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n|[[Action film|Action]]\n|[[Romance film|Romance]]\n|[[Crime film|Crime]]\n}}\n| creator                  = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Jojo Tidakorn Pookaothong\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 =  {{ubl\n|[[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]]\n|[[Way-Ar Sangngern]]\n)|[[Tawan Vihokratana]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = ''Fahk Welah (\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32)'' by The White Hair Cut\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[Thailand]]\n| language                 = Thai\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = 10\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = \n| editor                   = \n| location                 = [[Thailand]]\n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 50 minutes\n| company                  = [[GMMTV]]<br>Trasher Bangkok\n| distributor              = \n| channel                  = One31<br>[[Line TV|LINE TV]] (repeats)\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = <!-- The nation in which the series first aired, if different from country parameter. -->\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|08|09|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2019|10|11|df=yes}}\n| website                  = https://www.one31.net/shows/detail/289\n| website_title            = One31 Show Details\n| production_website       = https://tv.line.me/3willbefree\n| production_website_title = 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - LINE TV\n}}\n\n'''''3 Will Be Free''''' (from {{lang-th|\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14}}; {{RTGS|''Sam Rao Tong Rot''}}), is a 2019 [[Thailand|Thai]] [[action drama]] [[television series]] starring [[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]] (Mild), [[Way-ar Sangngern]] (Joss) and [[Tawan Vihokratana]] (Tay). The series, directed by Jojo Tidakorn Pookaothong and produced by [[GMMTV]], premiered in [[Thailand]] and aired on [[One31]] from August 9, 2019 to October 11, 2019 with repeats on [[Line TV|LINE TV]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c-\u0e40\u0e15-\u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a\" \u0e1f\u0e32\u0e14\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1d\u0e35\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e14\u0e38\u0e40\u0e14\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e14!!! \u0e43\u0e19\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c \"3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\" \u0e40\u0e23\u0e34\u0e48\u0e21 9 \u0e2a\u0e34\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49 |url=http://www.gmm-tv.com/news.php?id=1717 |website=gmm-tv.com |publisher=GMMTV |accessdate=18 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\u201d \u0e01\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e43\u0e04\u0e23 \u201c\u0e40\u0e15, \u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a, \u0e40\u0e08\u0e19\u0e19\u0e35\u0e48 \u0e2f\u0e25\u0e2f\u201d \u0e19\u0e33\u0e17\u0e35\u0e21\u0e1e\u0e39\u0e14\u0e04\u0e38\u0e22 \u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e25\u0e39\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e1e!!! |url=https://www.springnews.co.th/pr/526134 |website=springnews.co.th |publisher=[[Spring News]] |accessdate=18 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e15 \u0e40\u0e04\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e14\u0e08\u0e31\u0e14!!! \u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c \u0e42\u0e14\u0e19\u0e43\u0e1a\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e48\u0e07\u0e08\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e15\u0e32\u0e22 \u0e25\u0e38\u0e49\u0e19\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e07\u0e17\u0e49\u0e32\u0e22 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 |url=https://www.newsplus.co.th/176156 |website=newsplus.co.th |publisher=News Plus |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIt was one of the 13 television series for 2019 launched by GMMTV during their \"Wonder Th13teen\" event last November 5, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 13 \u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48 2019 \u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e46 \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e22\u0e27\u0e32\u0e22\u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27\u0e1f\u0e34\u0e19\u0e15\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e14\u0e17\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e35 |url=http://www.thaiticketmajor.com/variety/ent/10470/ |website=thaiticketmajor.com |accessdate=12 December 2019 |language=Thai}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e08\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e21\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e21\u0e17\u0e35\u0e27\u0e35\" \u0e08\u0e31\u0e14\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e0d\u0e48 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 13 \u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48 \u0e1b\u0e35 2019 |url=https://www.springnews.co.th/entertain/fiction/378681 |website=springnews.co.th |publisher=[[Spring News]] |accessdate=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nNeo ([[Way-ar Sangngern]]), a bisexual male stripper/prostitute, begins an affair with Vanika ([[Inthira Charoenpura]]), a famous actress and the second wife of Sia Thana ([[Sarut Vijittranon]]), a real estate mogul and mob kingpin. Phon ([[Natthawut Jenmana]]) and Ter ([[Chanagun Arpornsutinan]]), the two hitmen working for Thana, are tasked to kill Neo and punish Vanika. Upon finding the pair, Ter tries to shoot Neo, but accidentally shoots and kills Vanika instead. Neo runs to the strip club where he works and is followed by Phon; earlier, Shin ([[Tawan Vihokratana]]), Thana's only son who happens to be a reluctant heir of his father's mob empire, comes to the same bar with his friends and meets Miw ([[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]]), a hostess at the bar. Shin's friends pay Miw to sleep with Shin (unbeknownst to them, Shin is gay, and doesn't actually sleep with Miw). Afterwards, Shin and Miw both return to the bar. In the bathroom, Shin runs into Neo, who is hiding from Phon, and who has apparently met Shin before (this is revealed later in the series). Phon discovers them, but is stopped by Miw, who accidentally shoots and kills Phon.  Neo, Miw, and Shin escape together and begin a harrowing journey that takes them from a seedy [[Bangkok]] motel, to the jungle and to the ocean as they try to evade those who are trying to find them.  \n\nPhon's death devastates not only Ter, but Phon's lover, Mae ([[Watchara Sukchum]]), a transgender female waitress who has long wanted Phon to leave the life of a gangster. Mae and Ter vow to take revenge on Phon's killers and follow the trio to the jungle, where they are hiding out with the assistance of Leo ([[Suphakorn Sriphothong]]), Neo's brother. The trio also seeks refuge in Miw's hometown and receives help from her ex-boyfriend, Luang ([[Pumipat Paiboon]]), while simultaneously dealing with Boss John, a mob leader in direct conflict with Thana, and the brother of Miw's step-father (who had tried to rape her years earlier and was accidentally killed by Miw). As their survival adventure continues, the trio develop strong feelings of friendship and loyalty towards each other with Neo, Miw, and Shin finding themselves in a love triangle. By the end of the series, all three must face the repercussions of their actions and the actions of others.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\nBelow are the cast of the series:<ref>{{cite web |title=3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 [Official Trailer] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ct9fPlMJSDw |website=youtube.com |publisher=[[GMMTV]] |accessdate=7 April 2020 |date=9 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c-\u0e40\u0e15-\u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a\" \u0e1f\u0e32\u0e14\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1d\u0e35\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e14\u0e38\u0e40\u0e14\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e14!!! |url=https://www.newsplus.co.th/171951 |website=newsplus.co.th |publisher=News Plus |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n=== Main ===\n* [[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]] (Mild) as Miw\n* [[Way-ar Sangngern]] (Joss) as Neo\n* [[Tawan Vihokratana]] (Tay) as Shin\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Watchara Sukchum]] (Jennie Panhan) as Mae\n* [[Chanagun Arpornsutinan]] (Gunsmile) as Tur\n* [[Natthawut Jenmana]] (Max) as Phon\n* [[Pumipat Paiboon]] (Prame) as Luang\n* [[Suphakorn Sriphothong]] (Podd) as Leo (Neo's brother)\n* [[Jirakit Kuariyakul]] (Toptap) as PP\n* [[Sivakorn Lertchoochot]] (Guy) as Touch\n* [[Harit Cheewagaroon]] (Sing) as James\n* [[Naphon Phromsuwan]] (Stop) as Boss John\n* [[Sarut Vijittranon]] (Big) as Sia Thana\n* [[Inthira Charoenpura]] as Vanika (Thana's Wife)\n* [[Sarocha Watitapun]] (Tao)\n* [[Penpak Sirikul]] as Miw's mother\n* [[Arisara Wongchalee]] (Fresh)\n* [[Krittanai Arsalprakit]] (Nammon) as Ken\n\n=== Guest role ===\n* [[Theepisit Mahaneeranon]] (Frame)\n* [[Pronpiphat Pattanasettanon]] (Plustor) as Nurse/Hitman\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Song Title\n!Romanized Title\n!Artist(s)\n!Ref\n|-\n| ''\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32''\n| ''Fahk Welah''\n| The White Hair Cut\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32 Ost.3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - The White Hair Cut |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5w-nDbr2fxY |website=youtube.com |publisher=[[GMMTV]] Records |accessdate=19 November 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Award Ceremony\n!Category\n!Recipient(s)\n!Result\n!Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |2020\n| LINE TV Awards 2020\n| Best Kiss Scene\n| ''3 Will Be Free''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=LINE TV AWARDS 2020 \u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25\u0e43\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e35\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e08\u0e30\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e43\u0e04\u0e23 |url=https://www.beartai.com/lifestyle/404837 |website=beartai.com |publisher=Beartai |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=15 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e23\u0e38\u0e1b\u0e1c\u0e25\u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25 LINE TV AWARDS 2020 \u0e01\u0e25\u0e31\u0e1f-\u0e21\u0e34\u0e27, \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e21-\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e07\u0e42\u0e15, \u0e2d\u0e2d\u0e1f-\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e19\u0e32\u0e14\u0e32\u0e27 \u0e04\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25\u0e40\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e01\u0e40\u0e2a\u0e35\u0e22\u0e07\u0e01\u0e23\u0e35\u0e4a\u0e14\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e15\u0e32\u0e21\u0e04\u0e32\u0e14 |url=https://thestandard.co/line-tv-awards-2020/ |website=thestandard.co |publisher=The Standard |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.one31.net/shows/detail/289 One31 Show Details]\n* [https://tv.line.me/3willbefree 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - LINE TV]\n* {{IMDb title | id= tt11025732 | title= 3 Will Be Free}}\n* [http://www.gmm-tv.com GMMTV]\n\n{{GMMTV television series|state=expanded}}\n[[Category:Television series by GMMTV]]\n[[Category:Thai LGBT-related television shows]]\n[[Category:2019 Thai television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2019 Thai television series endings]]\n[[Category:One31 television programmes]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related drama television series]]\n[[Category:Thai action television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Thai action drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = 3 Will Be Free\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|th|\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14}}\n| image                    = 3 Will Be Free poster.jpg\n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = {{ubl\n|[[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n|[[Action film|Action]]\n|[[Romance film|Romance]]\n|[[Crime film|Crime]]\n}}\n| creator                  = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Jojo Tidakorn Pookaothong\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 =  {{ubl\n|[[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]]\n|[[Way-Ar Sangngern]]\n)|[[Tawan Vihokratana]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = ''Fahk Welah (\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32)'' by The White Hair Cut\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[Thailand]]\n| language                 = Thai\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = 10\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = \n| editor                   = \n| location                 = [[Thailand]]\n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 50 minutes\n| company                  = [[GMMTV]]<br>Trasher Bangkok\n| distributor              = \n| channel                  = One31<br>[[Line TV|LINE TV]] (repeats)\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = <!-- The nation in which the series first aired, if different from country parameter. -->\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|08|09|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2019|10|11|df=yes}}\n| website                  = https://www.one31.net/shows/detail/289\n| website_title            = One31 Show Details\n| production_website       = https://tv.line.me/3willbefree\n| production_website_title = 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - LINE TV\n}}\n\n'''''3 Will Be Free''''' (from {{lang-th|\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14}}; {{RTGS|''Sam Rao Tong Rot''}}), is a 2019 [[Thailand|Thai]] [[action drama]] [[television series]] starring [[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]] (Mild), [[Way-ar Sangngern]] (Joss) and [[Tawan Vihokratana]] (Tay). The series, directed by Jojo Tidakorn Pookaothong and produced by [[GMMTV]], premiered in [[Thailand]] and aired on [[One31]] from August 9, 2019 to October 11, 2019 with repeats on [[Line TV|LINE TV]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c-\u0e40\u0e15-\u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a\" \u0e1f\u0e32\u0e14\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1d\u0e35\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e14\u0e38\u0e40\u0e14\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e14!!! \u0e43\u0e19\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c \"3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\" \u0e40\u0e23\u0e34\u0e48\u0e21 9 \u0e2a\u0e34\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49 |url=http://www.gmm-tv.com/news.php?id=1717 |website=gmm-tv.com |publisher=GMMTV |accessdate=18 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14\u201d \u0e01\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e43\u0e04\u0e23 \u201c\u0e40\u0e15, \u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a, \u0e40\u0e08\u0e19\u0e19\u0e35\u0e48 \u0e2f\u0e25\u0e2f\u201d \u0e19\u0e33\u0e17\u0e35\u0e21\u0e1e\u0e39\u0e14\u0e04\u0e38\u0e22 \u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e01\u0e0b\u0e4c\u0e04\u0e25\u0e39\u0e0b\u0e35\u0e1e!!! |url=https://www.springnews.co.th/pr/526134 |website=springnews.co.th |publisher=[[Spring News]] |accessdate=18 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e15 \u0e40\u0e04\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e14\u0e08\u0e31\u0e14!!! \u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c \u0e42\u0e14\u0e19\u0e43\u0e1a\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e48\u0e07\u0e08\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e15\u0e32\u0e22 \u0e25\u0e38\u0e49\u0e19\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e07\u0e17\u0e49\u0e32\u0e22 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 |url=https://www.newsplus.co.th/176156 |website=newsplus.co.th |publisher=News Plus |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIt was one of the 13 television series for 2019 launched by GMMTV during their \"Wonder Th13teen\" event last November 5, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 13 \u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48 2019 \u0e41\u0e1f\u0e19\u0e46 \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e22\u0e27\u0e32\u0e22\u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27\u0e1f\u0e34\u0e19\u0e15\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e14\u0e17\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e35 |url=http://www.thaiticketmajor.com/variety/ent/10470/ |website=thaiticketmajor.com |accessdate=12 December 2019 |language=Thai}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e08\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e21\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e47\u0e21\u0e17\u0e35\u0e27\u0e35\" \u0e08\u0e31\u0e14\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e0d\u0e48 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 13 \u0e0b\u0e35\u0e23\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e4c\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e48 \u0e1b\u0e35 2019 |url=https://www.springnews.co.th/entertain/fiction/378681 |website=springnews.co.th |publisher=[[Spring News]] |accessdate=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nNeo ([[Way-ar Sangngern]]), a bisexual male stripper/prostitute, begins an affair with Vanika ([[Inthira Charoenpura]]), a famous actress and the second wife of Sia Thana ([[Sarut Vijittranon]]), a real estate mogul and mob kingpin. Phon ([[Natthawut Jenmana]]) and Ter ([[Chanagun Arpornsutinan]]), the two hitmen working for Thana, are tasked to kill Neo and punish Vanika. Upon finding the pair, Ter tries to shoot Neo, but accidentally shoots and kills Vanika instead. Neo runs to the strip club where he works and is followed by Phon; earlier, Shin ([[Tawan Vihokratana]]), Thana's only son who happens to be a reluctant heir of his father's mob empire, comes to the same bar with his friends and meets Miw ([[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]]), a hostess at the bar. Shin's friends pay Miw to sleep with Shin (unbeknownst to them, Shin is gay, and doesn't actually sleep with Miw). Afterwards, Shin and Miw both return to the bar. In the bathroom, Shin runs into Neo, who is hiding from Phon, and who has apparently met Shin before (this is revealed later in the series). Phon discovers them, but is stopped by Miw, who accidentally shoots and kills Phon.  Neo, Miw, and Shin escape together and begin a harrowing journey that takes them from a seedy [[Bangkok]] motel, to the jungle and to the ocean as they try to evade those who are trying to find them.  \n\nPhon's death devastates not only Ter, but Phon's lover, Mae ([[Watchara Sukchum]]), a transgender female waitress who has long wanted Phon to leave the life of a gangster. Mae and Ter vow to take revenge on Phon's killers and follow the trio to the jungle, where they are hiding out with the assistance of Leo ([[Suphakorn Sriphothong]]), Neo's brother. The trio also seeks refuge in Miw's hometown and receives help from her ex-boyfriend, Luang ([[Pumipat Paiboon]]), while simultaneously dealing with Boss John, a mob leader in direct conflict with Thana, and the brother of Miw's step-father (who had tried to rape her years earlier and was accidentally killed by Miw). As their survival adventure continues, the trio develop strong feelings of friendship and loyalty towards each other with Neo, Miw, and Shin finding themselves in a love triangle. By the end of the series, all three must face the repercussions of their actions and the actions of others.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\nBelow are the cast of the series:<ref>{{cite web |title=3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 [Official Trailer] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ct9fPlMJSDw |website=youtube.com |publisher=[[GMMTV]] |accessdate=7 April 2020 |date=9 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u0e21\u0e32\u0e22\u0e14\u0e4c-\u0e40\u0e15-\u0e08\u0e2d\u0e2a\" \u0e1f\u0e32\u0e14\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e19\u0e1d\u0e35\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e36\u0e01\u0e14\u0e38\u0e40\u0e14\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e14!!! |url=https://www.newsplus.co.th/171951 |website=newsplus.co.th |publisher=News Plus |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n=== Main ===\n* [[Lapassalan Jiravechsoontornkul]] (Mild) as Miw\n* [[Way-ar Sangngern]] (Joss) as Neo\n* [[Tawan Vihokratana]] (Tay) as Shin\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Watchara Sukchum]] (Jennie Panhan) as Mae\n* [[Chanagun Arpornsutinan]] (Gunsmile) as Tur\n* [[Natthawut Jenmana]] (Max) as Phon\n* [[Pumipat Paiboon]] (Prame) as Luang\n* [[Suphakorn Sriphothong]] (Podd) as Leo (Neo's brother)\n* [[Jirakit Kuariyakul]] (Toptap) as PP\n* [[Sivakorn Lertchoochot]] (Guy) as Touch\n* [[Harit Cheewagaroon]] (Sing) as James\n* [[Naphon Phromsuwan]] (Stop) as Boss John\n* [[Sarut Vijittranon]] (Big) as Sia Thana\n* [[Inthira Charoenpura]] as Vanika (Thana's Wife)\n* [[Sarocha Watitapun]] (Tao)\n* [[Penpak Sirikul]] as Miw's mother\n* [[Arisara Wongchalee]] (Fresh)\n* [[Krittanai Arsalprakit]] (Nammon) as Ken\n\n=== Guest role ===\n* [[Theepisit Mahaneeranon]] (Frame)\n* [[Pronpiphat Pattanasettanon]] (Plustor) as Nurse/Hitman\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Song Title\n!Romanized Title\n!Artist(s)\n!Ref\n|-\n| ''\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32''\n| ''Fahk Welah''\n| The White Hair Cut\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e1d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e40\u0e27\u0e25\u0e32 Ost.3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - The White Hair Cut |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5w-nDbr2fxY |website=youtube.com |publisher=[[GMMTV]] Records |accessdate=19 November 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Award Ceremony\n!Category\n!Recipient(s)\n!Result\n!Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |2020\n| LINE TV Awards 2020\n| Best Kiss Scene\n| ''3 Will Be Free''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=LINE TV AWARDS 2020 \u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25\u0e43\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e35\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e08\u0e30\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e43\u0e04\u0e23 |url=https://www.beartai.com/lifestyle/404837 |website=beartai.com |publisher=Beartai |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=15 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0e2a\u0e23\u0e38\u0e1b\u0e1c\u0e25\u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25 LINE TV AWARDS 2020 \u0e01\u0e25\u0e31\u0e1f-\u0e21\u0e34\u0e27, \u0e42\u0e2d\u0e21-\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e07\u0e42\u0e15, \u0e2d\u0e2d\u0e1f-\u0e01\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e19\u0e32\u0e14\u0e32\u0e27 \u0e04\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\u0e23\u0e32\u0e07\u0e27\u0e31\u0e25\u0e40\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e01\u0e40\u0e2a\u0e35\u0e22\u0e07\u0e01\u0e23\u0e35\u0e4a\u0e14\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e15\u0e32\u0e21\u0e04\u0e32\u0e14 |url=https://thestandard.co/line-tv-awards-2020/ |website=thestandard.co |publisher=The Standard |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=Thai |date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.one31.net/shows/detail/289 One31 Show Details]\n* [https://tv.line.me/3willbefree 3 Will Be Free \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e21\u0e40\u0e23\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e14 - LINE TV]\n* {{IMDb title | id= tt11025732 | title= 3 Will Be Free}}\n* [http://www.gmm-tv.com GMMTV]\n\n[[Category:Television series by GMMTV]]\n[[Category:Thai LGBT-related television shows]]\n[[Category:2019 Thai television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2019 Thai television series endings]]\n[[Category:One31 television programmes]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related drama television series]]\n[[Category:Thai action television series]]\n", "name_user": "Emperork", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3_Will_Be_Free"}
{"title_page": "Balearic Islands (Congress of Deputies constituency)", "text_new": "Manoj kashyap madhakapurwa{{Infobox constituency\n| name           = Balearic Islands\n| type           = [[Congress of Deputies]]<br/>Electoral\n| image          = SpanishCongressDistricts(BalearicIslands).png\n| image_size     = 400px\n| caption        = Location of Balearic Islands within [[Spain]]ok jobs\n| district_label = [[Provinces of Spain|Province]]\n| district       = [[Balearic Islands]]\n| region_label   = [[Autonomous communities of Spain|Autonomous community]]\n| region         = [[Balearic Islands]]\n| population     = [[File:Green Arrow Up Darker.svg|10px]]1,149,460 (2019)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ine.es/jaxiT3/Datos.htm?t=2852 |title=Cifras oficiales de poblaci\u00f3n resultantes de la revisi\u00f3n del Padr\u00f3n municipal a 1 de enero. Poblaci\u00f3n por provincias y por sexo |language=Spanish |website=ine.es |publisher=[[Instituto Nacional de Estad\u00edstica (Spain)|National Institute of Statistics]] |access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n| electorate     = [[File:Green Arrow Up Darker.svg|10px]]807,170 (Nov 2019)\n| towns          = [[Palma de Mallorca|Palma]], [[Calvi\u00e0]], [[Ibiza (town)|Ibiza]]\n| year           = [[1977 Spanish general election|1977]]\n| seats          = 6 (1977\u20131993)<br/>7 (1993\u20132004)<br/>8 (2004\u2013present)\n| members        = {{unbulleted list\n | {{Color box|{{Spanish Socialist Workers' Party/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party|PSOE]] (2)\n | {{Color box|{{People's Party (Spain)/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[People's Party (Spain)|PP]] (2)\n | {{Color box|{{Unidas Podemos/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Unidas Podemos|UP]] (2)\n | {{Color box|{{Vox (political party)/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Vox (political party)|Vox]] (2)\n}}\n}}\nThe '''Balearic Islands''' ({{lang-ca|Illes Balears}}, {{lang-es|Islas Baleares}})\u2014'''Balearics''' until 2000 ({{lang-es|Baleares}}, {{lang-ca|Balears}})\u2014are one of the 52 constituencies ({{lang-es|circunscripciones}}) represented in the [[Congress of Deputies]], the lower chamber of the Spanish parliament, the [[Cortes Generales]]. The constituency currently elects eight [[Deputy (legislator)|deputies]]. Its boundaries correspond with those of the [[Balearic Islands]]. The [[electoral system]] uses the [[D'Hondt method]] and a [[Closed list|closed-list]] [[proportional representation]], with a minimum threshold of three percent.\n\n==Electoral system==\nThe constituency was created as per the [[1977 Political Reform Act|Political Reform Act 1977]] and was first contested in the [[1977 Spanish general election|1977 general election]]. The Act provided for the [[provinces of Spain]] to be established as multi-member districts in the [[Congress of Deputies]],<ref name=\"PRA77\">{{cite act |title=[[1977 Political Reform Act|Ley 1/1977, de 4 de enero, para la Reforma Pol\u00edtica]] |type=Law |number=1 |work=[[Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado]] |language=Spanish |date=4 January 1977 |url=https://www.boe.es/buscar/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1977-165 |access-date=27 December 2016}}</ref> with this regulation being maintained under the [[Spanish Constitution of 1978]]. Additionally, the Constitution requires for any modification of the provincial limits to be approved under an [[Organic Law (Spain)|organic law]], needing an [[absolute majority]] in the [[Cortes Generales]].<ref name=\"SpaCons\">{{cite act |title=[[Spanish Constitution of 1978|Constituci\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]] |work=Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado |language=Spanish |date=29 December 1978 |url=http://www.boe.es/buscar/act.php?id=BOE-A-1978-31229&p=20110927 |access-date=27 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nVoting is on the basis of [[universal suffrage]], which comprises all nationals over eighteen and in full enjoyment of their political rights. The only exception was in 1977, when this was limited to nationals ''over twenty-one'' and in full enjoyment of their political ''and'' civil rights. Amendments to the electoral law in 2011 required for [[Spanish diaspora|Spaniards abroad]] to [[Voter registration|apply for voting]] before being permitted to vote, a system known as \"begged\" or expat vote ({{lang-es|Voto rogado}}).<ref>{{cite web |last=Reig Pellicer |first=Naiara |date=16 December 2015 |url=http://www.cafebabel.co.uk/politics/article/spanish-elections-begging-for-the-right-to-vote.html |title=Spanish elections: Begging for the right to vote |website=cafebabel.co.uk |access-date=17 July 2017}}</ref> 348 seats are elected using the [[D'Hondt method]] and a [[closed list]] [[proportional representation]], with a [[election threshold|threshold]] of three percent of valid votes\u2014which includes blank ballots\u2014being applied in each constituency. Parties not reaching the threshold are not taken into consideration for seat distribution. Each provincial constituency is entitled to an initial minimum of two seats, with the remaining 248 being distributed in proportion to their populations. [[Ceuta]] and [[Melilla]] are allocated the two remaining seats, which are elected using [[plurality voting]].<ref name=\"SpaCons\"/><ref name=\"SpaELaw77\">{{cite act |title=Real Decreto-ley 20/1977, de 18 de marzo, sobre Normas Electorales |type=Royal Decree-Law |number=20 |work=Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado |language=Spanish |date=18 March 1977 |url=https://www.boe.es/buscar/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1977-7445 |access-date=14 December 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"SpaELaw85\">{{cite act |title=Ley Org\u00e1nica 5/1985, de 19 de junio, del R\u00e9gimen Electoral General |type=Organic Law |number=5 |work=Bolet\u00edn Oficial del Estado |language=Spanish |date=19 June 1985 |url=https://www.boe.es/buscar/act.php?id=BOE-A-1985-11672&tn=1&p=20190625 |access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> The use of the D'Hondt method may result in a higher effective threshold, depending on the [[district magnitude]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Gallagher |first=Michael |date=30 July 2012 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730092518/http://www.tcd.ie/Political_Science/staff/michael_gallagher/ElSystems/Docts/effthresh.php |title=Effective threshold in electoral systems |publisher=Trinity College, Dublin |access-date=22 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe electoral law allows for [[Political party|parties]] and [[Political alliance|federations]] registered in the [[Ministry of the Interior (Spain)|interior ministry]], [[Electoral alliance|coalitions]] and [[Grouping of electors (Spain)|groupings of electors]] to present lists of candidates. Parties and federations intending to form a coalition ahead of an election are required to inform the relevant Electoral Commission within ten days of the election call\u2014fifteen before 1985\u2014whereas groupings of electors need to secure the signature of at least one percent of the electorate in the constituencies for which they seek election\u2014one-thousandth of the electorate, with a compulsory minimum of 500 signatures, until 1985\u2014disallowing electors from signing for more than one list of candidates. Also since 2011, parties, federations or coalitions that have not obtained a mandate in either chamber of the Cortes at the preceding election are required to secure the signature of at least 0.1 percent of electors in the aforementioned constituencies.<ref name=\"SpaELaw77\"/><ref name=\"SpaELaw85\"/>\n\n==Deputies==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:97%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\"\n! colspan=\"3\"| [[Deputy (legislator)|Deputies]] 1977\u2013present\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"|\n{| class=\"navbox collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:100%; width:100%; float:left; border:0; margin-top:-1px;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#FDFDFD;\"| ''Key to parties''\n|-\n| style=\"font-size:95%; border:solid 1px silver; padding:8px; background:white;\"|\n{{div col|colwidth=7.5em}}\n{{legend|{{Unidas Podemos/meta/color}}|[[Units Podem M\u00e9s|UPM]]/[[Unidas Podemos|UP]]|border=1px