e Tough'', ''[[Uprising (novel)|Uprising]]'', ''Palace of Mirrors'', ''[[Claim to Fame]]'', ''The Always War'', ''Game Changer'', the [[Shadow Children]] series, and the Missing series. She also wrote ''[[Into the Gauntlet]]'', book 10 in the ''[[The 39 Clues|39 Clues]]'' series. Her books have made [[New York Times Best Seller|''New York Times'' Best Seller]] lists and [[American Library Association]] (ALA) annual book lists and they have won the International Reading Association's Children's Book Award and more than a dozen state reader's choice awards.<ref name=biog/>\n\nThe ''New York Times''\u2019 best-selling author currently lives in [[Columbus, Ohio]] with her husband, Doug, and their two children, Meredith and Connor.<ref name=\"famousauthors.org\"/>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n=== [[Shadow Children]] series ===\n* ''[[Among the Hidden]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Among the Impostors]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Among the Betrayed]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Among the Barons]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[Among the Brave]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Among the Enemy]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Among the Free]]'' (2006)\n\n=== The Palace Chronicles ===\n* ''[[Just Ella]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[Just Ella#Palace of Mirrors|Palace of Mirrors]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Just Ella#Palace of Lies|Palace of Lies]]'' (2015)\n\n=== [[The Missing (novel series)|The Missing]] series ===\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Found|Found]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Sent|Sent]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Sabotaged|Sabotaged]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Torn|Torn]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Caught|Caught]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Shorts|Sought]]'' (E-book short story, 2013)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Risked|Risked]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Shorts|Rescued]]'' (E-book short story, 2014)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Revealed|Revealed]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[The Missing (novel series)#Redeemed|Redeemed]]'' (2015)\n\n=== [[The 39 Clues]] series ===\n* ''[[Into 